/**
 * MMS PM Scheduler Service Unit Tests
 *
 * Tests for the PM Scheduler Service covering:
 * - Compliance window calculation (mileage OR time triggers)
 * - PM hierarchy handling (C4 satisfies C1/C2/C3)
 * - Track allocation and conflict detection
 * - Material constraint checking (hard 14 days, soft 90 days)
 * - Maximo lock validation
 * - PM scheduling operations (create, move, lock, unlock)
 * - Tactical scheduling runs
 *
 * This is a CRITICAL service for MMS:
 * - PM scheduling must respect compliance windows
 * - Higher-level PMs satisfy lower-level requirements (hierarchy)
 * - Material constraints can block scheduling
 * - Maximo locks prevent modification of in-progress work
 *
 * @see src/services/pm-scheduler.ts
 * @see specs/004-domain-services.md Section 4.4
 */

